ymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18702","n18703"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to probe into (a hole, like a well) so as to measure its depth; to gauge; to sound","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to probe into (a hole, like a well) so as to measure its depth; to gauge; to sound; to probe into (someone) as if measuring him; to gauge; to sound; to judge; to weigh up","tags":["figuratively","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَبَر (sabar) (form I), probing, prodding","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"measure, habit, form, appearance, garb, features, likeness, mien","tags":["countable","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"source, origin, root","tags":["countable","obsolete","transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic סְבַר (sḇar) in a very narrow meaning, apparently only back-formed from سِبَار (sibār), مِسْبَار (misbār), مِسْبَر (misbar, “probe”)."},"ipa":["/sa.ba.ra/","/sabr/","/sibr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18702","headword_ar":"سَبْرٌ","root":"sbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siborN","text_ar":"سِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Mu- ärrij, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n18703","headword_ar":"سِبْرٌ","root":"sbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saborN","text_ar":"سَبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"source,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"origin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a thing,] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSolN","text_ar":"اَصْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) pl. of both"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaArN","text_ar":"اَسْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearance; figure, feature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lineaments; external state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition; state with regard to apparel and the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly form"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearance"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aspect; garb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complexion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beauty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brightness of countenance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) pl. of both as above. (M.) ―         -b3-  IAar says, I heard Aboo-Ziyád El-Kilábee say, I returned from Marw to the desert, and one of its people said to me,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^am~aA","text_ar":"اَمَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~iboru faHaDariY~N waA^am~aA All~isaAnu fabadawiY~N","text_ar":"السِّبْرُ فَحَضَرِىٌّ وَاَمَّا اللِّسَانُ فَبَدَوِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As to garb and appearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thou art like]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an inhabitant of a town; but as to tongue, an inhabitant of the desert."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA.) ―         -b4-  You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Hasanu AlHibori","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ حَسَنُ الحِبْرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAls~ibori","text_ar":"وَالسِّبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is beautiful and of goodly appearance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiborN","text_ar":"حِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-  A woman of the desert said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojabaniY siboru fulaAnK","text_ar":"اَعْجَبَنِى سِبْرُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The good condition, and flourishing state of body, of such a one pleased me: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhu say~iy^a Als~ibori","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُ سَيِّيَ السِّبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw him to have an altered and ill appearance of body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus she assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbr","text_ar":"سبر"},{"kind":"text","text":"two significations. (TA.) ―         -b6-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laHasanu Als~ibori","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَحَسَنُ السِّبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is goodly in complexion and appearance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siborN","text_ar":"سِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A characteristic by which one knows the generousness or ungenerousness of a beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, M.) ―         -b8-  And (assumed tropical:)  One's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge of the fruitfulness or unfruitfulness"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the good or bad condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA.) ―         -b9-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Likeness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abahN","text_ar":"شَبَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA. [In some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sub~apN","text_ar":"سُبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is an evident mistake.]) So in the phrase, occurring in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galaba Ealayohimo siboru A^abiY bakorK","text_ar":"غَلَبَ عَلَيْهِمْ سِبْرُ اَبِى بَكْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The likeness"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abah","text_ar":"شَبَه"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Aboo-Bekr predominated in them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earafahu bisibori A^abiyhi","text_ar":"عَرَفَهُ بِسِبْرِ اَبِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He knew him by the appearance and likeness of his father."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b10-  Also the former ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siborN","text_ar":"سِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Enmity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) accord. to El-Muärrij; but Az says that this is strange. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}